task.summary: Default task
Put back initialisation of new note edittext as Its used to get the contents of the 'quicknote' to pass through to the createNoteActivity.

Switched CreateBook from fragment to activity. Fixed bug where the finished date was being reset to today everytime a finished book was viewed. Created interface so both activities & fragments can use the same date picker.
Replaced fragment with activity.
Replaced book details fragment with activity.
Added back icon to navbar on bookdetails page.
Wait until the ViewPager child element has created the ProgressFragment and knows where to put the shared image before starting the animation/drawing the screen.
Removed picasso image cropping so that the image display amount/shape stays the same across the two views it now animates.
Experimenting with controlling the flow of animations around the shared object (book cover).
Added up action to create new book. Added settings activity to house the export/import to/from csv.
deleted templated settings activity.
Created settings activity (v2) to house data backup. Gave it the generic toolbar & navigation drawer.
Implemented listeners for the settings preferences. started building reading data csv builder.
Map the book records into their counterpart csv format.
Removed unnecessary slashes & log out csv results.
Added snackbar to (temporarily) publish results set.
Switched to use HTML format instead of CSV as google sheets doesn't have a mechanism of accepting a new line token for CSV's. Ridiculous.
Copy the export data HTML to the users clipboard so they can do something with it whilst I ruminate on a google drive sdk integration.
Reordered colums to make the speadsheet really nice and readable/useful outside of this apps use-case. Formatted date to a simpler more human friendly format.
Dynamically assign the parent/up behaviour as create book can be invoked from two activities.
Toned down animations when viewing book details. This requires some choreography before i'll be happy with it (I'm looking at you scrollBar).
Limit quicknote to one line of visible content (makes sense given the context).
Created new activity to host google books api book search to add new book.
Implemented 'X' to clear search. Added means of reaching this new action (will probably change this to have a FAB sub-menu withthe two add book methods).
Added nav bar up as home functionality for navigation consistency throughout the app.
Send through the intended status of the new book to be added.

Edit db schema to include ISBN, Description - I'm planning to integrate a few api's to retrieve/navigate user towards more book data on the web, so i need to save the ISBN & i'm considering adding the description to the progress view (since i'll have one from Google Books).
Perform an async task when typing in the search bo, this will house the books api HTTP GET
Using Google Books api for search.
There are alot of books out their. So I'll filter it down to 'only' the actual books (filtering out journals, magazines, etc).
Output the search results to the user!
Mapping out the search results authors list & ISBN.
Encore the user entered search string to remove spaces. Improved spacing around the results list items.
Further limit the wealth of written word searched here. Also added the limit, not certain what this actually should be yet (I'll probably up it to like 15?).
Create new book onClick, populating the returned fields
Populating all returned fields that i want to utilise. Fixed bug assigning new book status (was caused by changing a strings value not everywhere it was used).

Fixed regression where the date comparison was more exact then required which was causing the finished date to populate on the progress page before the user has actually defined the value for books added via search. Started introducing constants.
Extracting constants used throughout the app.
creating more constant strings, to make renaming safer.
Refactor to put the book creation incomplete control of the lifecycle when adding/deleting/updating a new book.
Add user feedback and don't attempt JSON parsing if the search has failed.
Hide the delete button behind the menu (I kept hitting it accidentally).
Deleted now unused string.
Add left|right padding to the search edit text
If a book has a valid finished date, don't set the default selection to today.
Display books description on the progress page (at the bottom)
Added button to the navbar to house the goodreads link.
Open link in a chrome webview (it offers speed benefits over opening the browser).
If a book doesn't have an ISBN stored, don't display the book link as it wont work.
Use GoodReads to dynamically generate url from isbn. Styling the custom webview.
